Chivo, I didn't mind the quality of the art.  It looks GOOD, especially the BOOM.   I also liked the interesting, well-done perspective on the truck as Chivo lifts it.<br>
<br>
In the future, though, Chivo, you might want to separate the frames in a more creative way.  You'll notice that in almost all cartoons, frames are separated by 2 black lines, with white space in between.  Without that white space, a casual reader can believe that the line is a wall or something.  2 frames get combined.<br>
---------<br>
Is it my imagination, or is my character a lard-@ss ? <br>
<br>
*grin-laughter*  He's got no butt at all, very little muscle, and this HUGE stomach hanging out.<br>
<br>
Can mechs drink beer ??? Eat pizza ?  Ice-cream ?<br>
Man, I need to go on a diet !<br>
<br>
Admittedly, I drew him with a big stomach, to make believable the physics of his overlapping-armadillo-plated-stomach.<br>
I just didn't realize that my character looks like... Santa Claus.  *laughter*<br>
--------<br>
Let's see... Chivo throws a truck onto me (ouch), and then shoots at the truck, to make it explode.  H'mmm... Let's think about those physics, for a moment.  He's standing NEXT to the truck when it explodes, and he's not shielded by ANYTHING.<br>
The explosion occurs near him, on his side of the truck,  because that's where he CAN shoot.<br>
<br>
I, on the other hand, am UNDER the truck, shielded by the engine block and the whole undercarriage.  The explosion will push down on me, but with an even pressure.  <br>
<br>
If I had a choice, I'd rather be MY character than Chivo's, during this explosion.<br>
<br>
Chivo's going to be pelted with flying fragments.<br>
MuuuuuHAHAHHAHAAAAAA !<br>
<br>
*ouch*<br>
